Diagnosis
. This species has a pronotum with translucent edge at its anterior and posterolateral sides and two expanded dark brown areas at the two flanks of semi-elliptical black central disc (
Fig. 54
). The new species has ventrites I–V dark brown and ventrites VI–VII yellow-brown (
Fig. 53
). The medial lobe of its male genitalia is only slightly constricted near apical 1/ 
6 in
dorsal aspect (
Figs. 55-57
).
